<br>
A mod rod stores 150 mana, a T Rod stores 660, to get at the mana, you need to spend health. Adding charges to the mod rod would actually make things easier, rather than just more convenient. This would suggest that if we want mod rods to be useful for mana recovery, the solution is to decrease the mana cost below 150, rather than increasing the amount of mana they can give back.<br>
<br>
For magicians themselves, a T Rod gives 260 mana for 900 hitpoints, ratio of .28. Picking a number of half the efficiency of T Rods, I get that mod rods should give 28 mana for 200 hitpoints, which would mean a mana cost of 122 mana. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarciuskarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arcius Karn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#333333>(3/30/02 2:39:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1190.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: PROPOSAL: Mini-T-Rods</span><hr size=1> I didn't think that the one costing a pearl was even dropping? <p><div align="center"><i><font size="-1">Arcius Karn</font></i>
